### Configure SQLite Database Connection

Source: https://laravel.com/docs/12.x/database

Set up SQLite database connection using environment variables. Specifies the database file path and optionally disables foreign key constraints. SQLite stores data in a single file on the filesystem.

```ini
DB_CONNECTION=sqlite
DB_DATABASE=/absolute/path/to/database.sqlite
```

--------------------------------

### Define Book Model with BelongsTo Author Relationship in Laravel Eloquent

Source: https://laravel.com/docs/12.x/eloquent-relationships

This PHP snippet defines an Eloquent `Book` model, including a `belongsTo` relationship method that links it to an `Author` model. This model setup is a prerequisite for demonstrating both lazy and eager loading of relationships.

```php
<?php

namespace App\Models;

use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Model;
use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Relations\BelongsTo;

class Book extends Model
{
    /**
     * Get the author that wrote the book.
     */
    public function author(): BelongsTo
    {
        return $this->belongsTo(Author::class);
    }
}
```

--------------------------------

### Authenticate User Instance

Source: https://laravel.com/docs/12.x/authentication

Set an existing user instance as the currently authenticated user by passing it to the Auth facade's login method. The user instance must implement the Illuminate\Contracts\Auth\Authenticatable contract, such as Laravel's App\Models\User model.

```APIDOC
## POST Auth::login()

### Description
Authenticate an existing user instance by setting it as the currently authenticated user. Useful after user registration or when a valid user instance is already available.

### Method
Facade Method

### Endpoint
Auth::login(user, remember)

### Parameters
#### Method Parameters
- **user** (Authenticatable) - Required - User instance implementing Illuminate\Contracts\Auth\Authenticatable contract
- **remember** (boolean) - Optional - Enable remember me functionality (default: false)

### Request Example
```php
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Auth;

Auth::login($user);

// With remember me functionality
Auth::login($user, $remember = true);

// With specific guard
Auth::guard('admin')->login($user);
```

### Response
#### Success Response
- **authenticated** (boolean) - User is now authenticated
- **user** (User) - The authenticated user instance

### Requirements
- User instance must implement Illuminate\Contracts\Auth\Authenticatable contract
- App\Models\User already implements this interface by default
```

